SIMPLE: hasty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hasty
<hw>Has"ty</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧s"t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Hastier</adjf>
<pr>(-t⟦icr⟧*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Hastiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[Akin to D. <ets>haastig</ets>,
G., Sw., & Dan. <ets>hastig</ets>. See <er>Haste</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Involving haste; done, made, etc.,
in haste; <as>as, a <ex>hasty</ex> retreat; a <ex>hasty</ex>
sketch</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Demanding haste or immediate action.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <au>Chaucer.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Hasty</xex>
employment.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Moving or acting with haste or in a hurry; hurrying;
hence, acting without deliberation; precipitate; rash; easily excited;
eager.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Seest thou a man that is <qex>hasty</qex> in his words? There is
more hope of a fool than of him.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. xxix.
20.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>hasty</qex> multitude⟦br⟧
Admiring entered.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be not <qex>hasty</qex> to go out of his sight.</q> <rj><qau>Eccl.
viii. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Made or reached without deliberation or due caution;
<as>as, a <ex>hasty</ex> conjecture, inference, conclusion, etc., a
<ex>hasty</ex> resolution.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Proceeding from, or indicating, a quick
temper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Take no unkindness of his <qex>hasty</qex> words.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Forward; early; first ripe.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧As the <xex>hasty</xex> fruit before the
summer.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Is. xxviii. 4.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hasty pudding</ent>⟦br⟧
